This paper deals with the problem of outsourcing secure and private machine learning computations, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on secure neural networks based classification algorithms, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of arithmetic computation over integers, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy concerns in sharing sensitive data, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
